---
title: Picker Group
---

p.-text
  | Picker groups are used to wrap a series of pickers on a single line.

h3 Examples
h4 Base
p.-text To render a picker group, wrap a series of pickers in a div and apply the class <code>m-pickerGroup</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup
      each type in ['Radio1','Radio2','Radio3']
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id=`ia-${type}`)
        label(for=`ia-${type}`)
          = type
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup">
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio1">
      <label for="radio1">
        Radio1
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio2">
      <label for="radio2">
        Radio2
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio3">
      <label for="radio3">
        Radio3
      </label>
    </div>

h3 Fluid
p.-text Picker groups can be expanded to fill the parent space by applying the class <code>-fluid</code>.
h4 Horizontal
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup.-fluid
      each type in ['Radio1','Radio2','Radio3']
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id=`ib-${type}`)
        label(for=`ib-${type}`)
          = type
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup -fluid">
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio1">
      <label for="radio1">
        Radio1
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio2">
      <label for="radio2">
        Radio2
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio3">
      <label for="radio3">
        Radio3
      </label>
    </div>

h4 Alignment
p.-text
  | Picker group text is centered by default. However, this behavior can change by applying the modifiers
  | <code>-align--left</code> or <code>-align--right</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup.-fluid
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='ic-Radio1')
        label.-align--left(for='ic-Radio1') Radio1
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='ic-Radio2')
        label(for='ic-Radio2') Radio2
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='ic-Radio3')
        label.-align--right(for='ic-Radio3') Radio3
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup -fluid">
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio1">
      <label class="-align--left" for="radio1">
        Radio1
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio2">
      <label for="radio2">
        Radio2
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio3">
      <label class="-align--right" for="radio3">
        Radio3
      </label>
    </div>

h4 Disable Fluidity
p.-text
  | To disable the fluidity of a specific picker in a fluid picker group, apply the class <code>-notFluid</code> to the picker.

.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    .m-pickerGroup.-fluid
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='id-Radio1')
        label(for='id-Radio1') Radio1
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='id-Radio2')
        label.-notFluid(for='id-Radio2') Radio2
        input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id='id-Radio3')
        label(for='id-Radio3') Radio3
  :code(lang='html')
    <div class="m-pickerGroup -fluid">
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio1">
      <label for="radio1">
        Radio1
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio2">
      <label class="-notFluid" for="radio2">
        Radio2
      </label>
      <input class="a-picker" type="radio" name="radios" id="radio3">
      <label for="radio3">
        Radio3
      </label>
    </div>

h3 Sizes

p.-text
  | Picker groups supports a full spectrum of sizes: <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>,
  |  <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>.
  | The default size is <code>-md</code>.

.example.-mb--3
  .-px--3.-pt--0.-pb--3
    each size in ['sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl']
      p.-text--bold= '-' + size
      .-d--flex.-flex--wrap
        .m-pickerGroup
          each type in ['Radio1','Radio2','Radio3']
            input.a-picker(type="radio", name='radios', id=`ie-${type}-${size}`)
            label(for=`ie-${type}-${size}`, class=`-${size}`)
                = type
  :code(lang='html')
    <!-- sm -->
    <div class="m-pickerGroup">
